{"scenario": "VIS-01", "turn_index": 0, "variant": "should i use minoxidil or finasteride for hair loss? compare them", "request": {"message": "should i use minoxidil or finasteride for hair loss? compare them", "conversation_id": "1626db60-bf9c-4bfa-9d74-720f20bd8539"}, "response_body": {"response": "minoxidil and finasteride work differently and often work best together, not as either/or.\n\n**minoxidil** stimulates hair follicles directly, regrowing hair faster (visible results in 3\u20134 months). it works on any hair loss type but requires daily application (topical or oral). side effects are rare.\n\n**finasteride** blocks dht, the hormone driving male-pattern hair loss. it's slower (6\u201312 months) but addresses the root cause. it's oral, once daily, but has sexual side effects in ~2% of users and only works for androgenetic alopecia.\n\n**the move:** if you have pattern hair loss, start finasteride (it's the only thing that stops progression long-term). add minoxidil if you want faster regrowth. if you're not sure what type of loss you have, see a derm first\u2014finasteride won't help non-hormonal loss.\n\nwhat's your hair loss pattern like, and have you seen a dermatologist yet?", "choices": [], "multi_choice": false, "input_widget": null, "progress": null, "products": [], "created_at": "2026-07-05T11:50:28.188865", "conversation_id": "1626db60-bf9c-4bfa-9d74-720f20bd8539", "confirm": null, "visual_blocks": [], "method_metadata": null}, "status_code": 200, "latency_s": 8.96, "transport_error": null, "checks": [{"name": "no_marker_leak", "passed": true, "detail": "clean"}, {"name": "no_leaked_json", "passed": true, "detail": "clean"}, {"name": "blocks_schema_valid", "passed": true, "detail": "clean"}, {"name": "no_tech_leak", "passed": true, "detail": "clean"}, {"name": "prose_nonempty", "passed": true, "detail": "len=883"}, {"name": "latency_lt", "passed": true, "detail": "9.0s (ceiling 60s)"}, {"name": "block_present", "passed": false, "detail": "types 